      "message": "If that is a concern then I\u0027m more in favour of applying it generally. Currently we \"flush the table\" (i.e. don\u0027t attempt to align columns) when the *number* of field names in column0 changes (this is why `\"main.example@v0\"` does *not* align with `\"v0.9.0\"`). We could pretty easily change this logic so that we flush the table whenever the actual field names don\u0027t match (maybe we want a more subtle rule: if col0 contains \u003e 1 field names then flush when rowN.col0.chain[len(self-2)] !\u003d rowM... I.e. the stem changes. Dunno - it\u0027s not obvious to me what the right thing is to do, so I suggest we revisit this if we come up with a rule that is simple that we all agree on.",
